Introduction

Miso (stylized as MiSO) is a South Korean rapper and singer under DOUBLE Entertainment. She is a former member of the girl groups GIRLS GIRLS and Ye-A.

She made her solo debut on April 10, 2017, with the single album "MiSO ALL ACCESS".

Miso was revealed as a member of GIRLS GIRLS on November 21, 2015. The group made their debut on December 9, 2015 with the single album "Strong Girls".

On February 10, 2019 DOUBLE Entertainment made an official statement announcing that Miso had decided to leave the group to focus on her solo career. Miso came back with the digital single album "ON N ON" nine days later on February 19, 2019.

In late October of 2022, she made her debut as a DJ under the stage name DJ RALLY, but she's still promoting under the name MiSO.
